This tournament brought together some of the strongest chess players of the time and helped solidify Steinitz's reputation as the leading chess player in the world at that point. It was an important event in the history of competitive chess and helped pave the way for the establishment of the World Chess Championship title that Steinitz would go on to win in 1886.
